%e A362817 For n = 9 the symmetric representation of sigma(9) has three parts from left to right as follows: a rectangle, a concave hexagon and a rectangle. The number of edges of the polygons are 4, 6, 4 respectively, so the row 9 of the triangle is [4, 6, 4].
